705207f-b.title: Brooklyn: Kings Highway - 6th Street
705207f-b.text:
(1)
King's Highway, north side, between West 6th and 7th Streets, showing the home of N. and G. Stillwell in 1860. This house which was erected in 1830, was demolished in 1926 to make way for a theatre, an
apartment house and a series of two family brick houses.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(2)
The same, taken from West 7th Street.
April 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(3)
The same, viewed from West 6th Street. The house in the rear
is on Quentin Road. It was demolished in 1926.
April 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
